# Apply Checklist (Worker Pre-Return Gate)

Read when: the local worker is about to mark a packet DONE.
Skip when: never for DONE packets.

Purpose: fixed ritual before the worker claims DONE. If any required item fails and cannot be repaired inside packet scope, return PARTIAL or BLOCKED, never DONE.

## Pre-Return Gate

### 1) Scope Discipline
- [ ] All edits stayed inside Allowed Files from `docs/WORKER_TASK_PACKET.md`
- [ ] No new file exceeds 400 lines
- [ ] No source file exceeds 500 lines unless packet authorized refactor

### 2) Path ID Evidence
- [ ] Every Path ID listed in the packet has a row in `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md`
- [ ] Smoke Coverage status is filled for each touched row
- [ ] Smoke command or runbook evidence recorded for each touched row

### 3) Validation Commands
Run only commands listed in the packet.
- [ ] Lint / format check
- [ ] Typecheck
- [ ] Targeted tests
- [ ] Required smoke IDs
- [ ] Final verify gate

### 3a) Visual / Human Smoke
If the packet changes UI, layout, navigation, user-facing copy, browser auth, or a visible workflow:
- [ ] Manual click path or browser smoke from the task packet was executed
- [ ] Expected visible result was observed
- [ ] Screenshot path, Playwright trace, or plain-English observation recorded in result packet

### 4) Test Honesty
- [ ] No assertion weakened to make a failing test pass
- [ ] No test deleted or skipped without packet authorization
- [ ] Test changes justified in result packet
- [ ] BUGFIX packets keep the regression test in the suite
- [ ] FEATURE / BUGFIX packets followed RED before GREEN
- [ ] New tests assert the real behavior or user outcome, not only that mocks, variables, or functions exist

### 4a) Data Rollback Safety
If the packet touches persistent data, migrations, schemas, seeds, file storage, external API contracts, or destructive writes:
- [ ] Pre-change snapshot/dump command from the packet was run or explicit N/A rationale recorded
- [ ] Snapshot artifact path or restore runbook recorded in result packet
- [ ] Rollback steps are executable by the operator without inventing SQL or code

### 5) Documentation Sync
If behavior, paths, commands, or workflows changed:
- [ ] `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md` updated
- [ ] `docs/SMOKE_TEST_CATALOG.md` updated when a new smoke is added
- [ ] `docs/WORKFLOW_TEST_MATRIX.md` updated when workflow verification changes
- [ ] `CHANGELOG.md` updated when behavior or operating model changes

### 6) Result Packet Filled
- [ ] Header echoes Packet ID and Packet Class
- [ ] Each acceptance criterion has PASS / FAIL and evidence pointer
- [ ] Iteration count <= Packet Class ceiling
- [ ] Diff stats included
- [ ] Body target <= 200 lines

### 7) Local Self-Review
- [ ] Fresh-context self-review executed
- [ ] Self-review result recorded
- [ ] Any flagged sections repaired or explicitly handed to orchestrator

## If Any Box Is Unchecked
- Scope, validation, or test-honesty failure -> return PARTIAL.
- Architecture or product ambiguity -> return BLOCKED.
- Missing required data snapshot or visual smoke evidence -> return PARTIAL unless the packet explicitly marked it N/A with rationale.
- Never return DONE with unchecked required boxes.
